# Test: two-tier dispatch delivers all routes under load with overflow
# VALIDATES: AC-10/AC-11/AC-12 -- burst exceeding per-peer pool triggers
#   overflow dispatch, all routes delivered without loss
# STATUS: Phase 6 (spec-ci-observer-per-test-audit) -- runtime_fail wired;
#         AC verification is TODO. Same architectural blocker as
#         forward-overflow-two-tier / community-strip: this test loads only
#         bgp-adj-rib-in and does NOT load any plugin that calls
#         ForwardUpdate, so the two-tier dispatch path is never exercised.
# PREVENTS: routes dropped during overflow, two-tier dispatch path untested
#   end-to-end through real reactor
#
# Flow:
# 1. ze.fwd.chan.size=2 forces a tiny per-worker channel (overflow guaranteed)
# 2. Source peer sends 80 UPDATEs in a burst
# 3. Routes would forward through ze to dest peer in the designed behaviour
# 4. Python observer smoke-checks metrics registration
# 5. AC-10/AC-11/AC-12 cannot be verified without a forwarding plugin

# Source peer (ASN 65001) -- sends 80 prefixes in a burst
option=env:var=ze.log.bgp.reactor.session:value=debug
stdin=source:terminator=EOF_SOURCE
option=tcp_connections:value=1
option=timeout:value=20s

